Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Spend seven (7) months in jail, under the Huber Law, to commence today at 3:00 p.m.;
2) AODA assessment and follow through counseling;
3) Have no contact with David Radant and Thomas Fagen except with approval through probation agent;
4) Pay costs of action;
5) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
7) Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge;
8) Maintain absolute sobriety;
9) Each year on probation, complete fifty (50) hours of community service work possibly educating others in this area;
10) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same.  
Court will leave open the issue regarding restitution for funeral expenses until it can be determined.  
Defendant is given three (3) days sentence credit.  
Cash bail to be applied to court costs and balance held until it is determined if restitution will owing. 
